| Microsoft/Samsung Ink Patent  Deal                                 |
|   from the so-happy-together dept.                                 |
|   posted by Zonk on Friday April 20, @12:04 (Patents)              |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/20/1440218          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader wrote with an article at ZDNet, discussing [0]further
implications of their patent cross-licensing initiative. With options
already in place with Fuji Xerox, the company is now signed up with
Samsung as well. From Samsung's perspective, it is simple: these deals
ensure it can sell products using Linux without facing a suit from the
Redmond-based corporation. "The notion that customers and businesses need
Microsoft's legal go-ahead to run Linux has been controversial for some
time, with the issue rising to the surface last November after Microsoft
reached an accord with Linux vendor Novell. Novell has since taken issue
with Microsoft's assertion that the deal represents an acknowledgment
that Linux infringes on Microsoft patents."

