+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| AMD Reports $611 Million Loss                                      |
|   from the just-a-little-bit-of-money dept.                        |
|   posted by Zonk on Friday April 20, @18:45 (AMD)                  |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/20/2115242     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

mpfife writes "Toms Hardware reports that [0]declining microprocessor
sales have pushed AMD deeply into the red. 'The company reported a net
loss of $611 million on revenues of $1.233 billion, which is more than
20% below the guidance the company expected at the end of Q4 2006. The
loss includes charges related to the ATI acquisition in the amount of
$113 million, but is mainly a result of the increasing competition with
Intel in the microprocessor market.'"

